    ],
    "http://ogp.me/ns#title": [
      {
        "@language": "en-ca",
        "@value": "Rhino | Out Innerspace | Nov 13 - 14, 2026 | Babs Asper Theatre"
      }
    ],
    "http://ogp.me/ns#image": [
      {
        "@language": "en-ca",
        "@value": "https://naccnaca-eventimages.s3.amazonaws.com/40370/rhino_by_out_innerspace_photo_of_adam_khazhmuradov_by_mark_kelly_1__large.jpg"
      }
    ],
    "http://ogp.me/ns#description": [
      {
        "@language": "en-ca",
        "@value": "A Lingering Lynchian Adventure\n\nThe imaginations of Tiffany Tregarthen and David Raymond, co-directors of Vancouver’s Out Innerspace, know no bounds. With a movement style marked by fluidity and plasticity they construct pieces that play with the subconscious and the surreal. Using evocative lighting as an emotional design language, their works combine a cinematic aesthetic with highly percussive physicality.\n\nIn Rhino an unlikely cast of characters past their prime — including a skeleton, rhino, and matador — jostle to maintain relevance; in their..."
      }
    ],
    "http://ogp.me/ns/fb#admins": [
      {
        "@language": "en-ca",
        "@value": "728780803"
      }
    ],
